ization and paved the way for the factory system.</p><p>Industrialization and the Factory System: Industrialization was a defining characteristic of the era of machineries. It brought about the shift from small-scale production in workshops to large-scale manufacturing in factories. The factory system centralized production processes, bringing together specialized machines, workers, and raw materials under one roof. This new mode of production led to increased efficiency, standardization, and the mass production of goods.</p>', 'Technology', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '116-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-07-14 14:45:41', '2023-07-14 14:45:41', '', 116, 'http://localhost/TheMillionVoice/?p=166', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
